   Sphingidae: Macroglossinae) collected in the Brazilian Atlantic Forest},
Journal = {INTEGRATIVE ZOOLOGY},
Year = {2024},
Volume = {19},
Number = {4},
Pages = {777-783},
Month = {JUL},
Abstract = {We recorded 14 pollen types belonging to 12 families of angiosperms.
   Pera (Peraceae) pollen type was found in all genera and was the most
   abundant. Our results suggest low specificity in the choice of flowers;
   thus, Sphingids with either short or long proboscises visited flowers of
   the same species. image},
